rust-proxmox-apt-api-types (3.0.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * APTRepositoryHandle changes from a flat enum to a struct over
    (repo_type, component) so adding a new Ceph release or product
    channel does not require fanning out enum variants. The kebab-case
    wire strings used by the REST API, perl, and the web UI are
    unchanged: enterprise, no-subscription, test, ceph-squid-enterprise,
    etc. all serialize/deserialize as before. Rust consumers that
    pattern-match on the old variant identifiers (e.g. `match handle
    { APTRepositoryHandle::CephSquidEnterprise => ... }`) will not
    compile any more; switch to matching on `handle.component()` (and,
    for Ceph, `handle.repo_type()`) instead. The fields are private and
    the struct is `#[non_exhaustive]` to keep all construction going
    through `APTRepositoryHandle::new` / `from_str` / the pub `const`
    instances, which all normalize the value to the wire-equivalent
    form.

  * Add APTRepoType enum (Pve, Pbs, Pdm, Pmg, Debian, DebianSecurity,
    DebianBackports, CephSquid, CephTentacle, ...) and APTRepoComponent
    enum (Enterprise, NoSubscription, Test, Main, Staging) as the two
    axes of the new handle struct. The type system allows arbitrary
    pairs; the set of semantically valid handles is constrained by the
    proxmox-apt-side STANDARD_REPOS lookup table, not by the types.

  * Add HostProduct enum (Pve, Pbs, Pdm, Pmg) for the host product an APT
    operation runs on behalf of. Replaces the previous untyped &str
    parameter on the proxmox-apt public API.

  * Lift DebianCodename out of proxmox-apt so it can appear in API
    parameter and response types. Reachable from proxmox-apt at the
    historical re-export path for source compatibility. Both Deserialize
    and TryFrom<&str> now lowercase the input before matching known
    codenames; TryFrom keeps Err-on-unknown semantics for strict
    suite-name callers, while Deserialize keeps the Unknown(s) wire
    fallback.

  * Drop the enum-fallback Cargo feature: the Unknown(String) forward-
    compat fallback variant is now unconditional on every open-enum
    type (APTRepoType, APTRepoComponent, DebianCodename, HostProduct),
    so a single dependency can not accidentally turn graceful tolerance
    back into a hard deserialization failure for future variants.

  * The Unknown(_) payload is now constrained to lowercase kebab-case
    (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9]*(-[a-z0-9]+)*$`), where the previous 2.0.4
    `enum-fallback` `UnknownEnumValue(FixedString)` accepted any UTF-8
    string up to 31 bytes. No production wire payload hits this in
    practice (all Proxmox-emitted handles are lowercase kebab-case), but
    downstream maintainers introducing new wire forms must keep them in
    that envelope to round-trip via the Unknown fallback.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Sun, 03 May 2026 12:00:00 +0200

